signal_description: The SIGNAL query is calculating the percentage of cases in the table 'defaultview-217' where the event 'Change Status to In Progress' occurs more than once. It does this by first counting the total number of cases (case_id). Then, it filters out the cases where the event 'Change Status to In Progress' (event_name) occurs more than once. The count of these filtered cases is then divided by the total number of cases and multiplied by 100 to get the percentage. The result will be the percentage of cases where the event 'Change Status to In Progress' happens more than once.

SIGNAL query: 
SELECT COUNT(case_id) 
FILTER (
	WHERE (SELECT count(event_name) WHERE event_name = 'Change Status to In Progress' ) > 1 )
/ COUNT(case_id)
* 100
FROM "defaultview-217"
